  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Government of the Republic of Korea Support for the Joint Response Plan (JRP) 2020 Rohingya Humanitarian Crisis</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With approximately 1.2 million Rohingya and Bangladeshi Host Community individuals residing in and adjacent to the refugee camps, proper infrastructure with equitable access for all beneficiaries is crucial to the well-being of affected populations and the success of humanitarian interventions. Repair and recovery works, earthworks and site preparation, drainage channels and outfalls, bridge solutions and capacity development programmes are undertaken to contribute to beneficiary well-being and the effectiveness of response activities. This project aims to improve site safety, shelter quality, and household living conditions for women, girls, men and boys at the Rohingya refugees camps in Bangladesh by ensuring maintenance and upgrades of shelters with quality materials distributed with in-kind and voucher system and technical trainings as well as cash for work activities to support vulnerable families.</narrative>
  </description>
